model.text: ID of the model to use. Currently only gpt-3.5-turbo and gpt-3.5-turbo-0301 are supported

messages.text: The messages to generate chat completions for; in the chat format

temperature.text: What sampling temperature to use between 0 and 2. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random; while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. We generally recommend altering this or top_p but not both.

top_p.text: An alternative to sampling with temperature; called nucleus sampling; where the model considers the results of the tokens with top_p probability mass. So 0.1 means only the tokens comprising the top 10% probability mass are considered. We generally recommend altering this or temperature but not both.

n.text: How many chat completion choices to generate for each input message.

stream.text: If set; partial message deltas will be sent like in ChatGPT. Tokens will be sent as data-only server-sent events as they become available; with the stream terminated by a data - [DONE] message.

stop.text: Up to 4 sequences where the API will stop generating further tokens.

max_tokens.text: The maximum number of tokens allowed for the generated answer. By default the number of tokens the model can return will be (4096 - prompt tokens).

presence_penalty.text: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on whether they appear in the text so far; increasing the model's likelihood to talk about new topics.

frequency_penalty.text: Number between -2.0 and 2.0. Positive values penalize new tokens based on their existing frequency in the text so far; decreasing the model's likelihood to repeat the same line verbatim.

logit_bias.text: Modify the likelihood of specified tokens appearing in the completion. Accepts a json object that maps tokens (specified by their token ID in the tokenizer) to an associated bias value from -100 to 100. Mathematically the bias is added to the logits generated by the model prior to sampling. The exact effect will vary per model; but values between -1 and 1 should decrease or increase likelihood of selection; values like -100 or 100 should result in a ban or exclusive selection of the relevant token.

user.text: A unique identifier representing your end-user which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse

functions.text: A list of functions the model may generate JSON inputs for

function_call.text: Controls how the model responds to function calls

meta.description:
Creates a completion for the chat message.


List of available models for ChatGPT API:  


`gpt-3.5-turbo` (Current)

`gpt-3.5-turbo-16k`

`gpt-3.5-turbo-instruct`


`gpt-4` 

`gpt-4-32k`

`gpt-4-1106-preview`

`gpt-4-vision-preview`


[Official OpenAI model here: https://platform.openai.com/docs/models](https://platform.openai.com/docs/models)

create_chat_completion.auth_config:
[
            {
                "name": "api_key",
                "type": "input",
                "field": "input",
                "label": "OpenAI API Key",
                "message": "This API key will be used for accessing OpenAI APIs.",
                "required": true,
                "className": "",
                "placeholder": "sk-xxxxx"
            }
]

chat_id.text: Required. Unique identifier for the target chat or username of the target channel (in the format @channelusername)

message_thread_id.text: Optional. Unique identifier for the target message thread (topic) of the forum; for forum supergroups only

text.text: Required. Text of the message to be sent 1-4096 characters after entities parsing

parse_mode.text: Optional. Mode for parsing entities in the message text. See formatting options for more details.

entities.text: Optional. A JSON-serialized list of special entities that appear in message text which can be specified instead of parse_mode

disable_web_page_preview.text: Optional. Disables link previews for links in this message

disable_notification.text: Optional. Sends the message silently. Users will receive a notification with no sound.

protect_content.text: Optional. Protects the contents of the sent message from forwarding and saving

reply_to_message_id.text: Optional. If the message is a reply ID of the original message

allow_sending_without_reply.text: Optional. Pass True if the message should be sent even if the specified replied-to message is not found

reply_markup.text: Optional. Additional interface options. A JSON-serialized object for an inline keyboard custom reply keyboard instructions to remove reply keyboard or to force a reply from the user.

meta.description: Use this method to send text messages. On success, the sent Message is returned.

Destination.text: An object that contains the recipients of the email message

FeedbackForwardingEmailAddress.text: The address that you want bounce and complaint notifications to be sent to

FeedbackForwardingEmailAddressIdentityAr.text: This parameter is used only for sending authorization

FromEmailAddress.text: The email address to use as the "From" address for the email

FromEmailAddressIdentityArn.text: This parameter is used only for sending authorization

ListManagementOptions.text: An object used to specify a list or topic to which an email belongs

ReplyToAddresses.text: The "Reply-to" email addresses for the message

meta.description:
Screenshot any website, using http url.

Required:

`url`: A valid website url for screenshot. Example: url=https://openai.com



Optional:


`vw`: Use a number value to decide the width of the image.

`vh`: Use a number value to decide the height of the image.

`scale`: Use this to decide the quality of the image. Default : 2

`download`: Use this to download image in browser. Default : false

`file_type`: Select format of image, supported values: png, jpeg, webp. Default : png

`file_name`: Give your screenshot a name, applicable for download only.
